n radiation and a plentiful fuel stock (we have a lot of boron) make it the 'holy grail' of fusion power. <p>&quot;If,&quot; he wispered, &quot;if we could only pick that lock....&quot; - , THE WORLD SET FREE</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whitestar60>whitestar60</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/18/03 6:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=127>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Here is a plan for a nuclear thermal rocket space launch</span><hr size=1> [qoute]A source I found listed that a total of 8.7 MeV is released in the form of kenetic energy in alpha particles. Unlike energy in neutrons or photons, all the energy in the alphas can be recovered. [/qoute]<br>
<br>
